Command.Name: WriteRCDBrightness

Pointer.Name: brightness
Pointer.Comment:
In non-Gen 5 Lite mirrors, a brightness value of 0-255 sets the RCD PWM. Brightness value of > 255 restores micro control of the PWM. The RCD will be forced on and will use an independently-pulsed glare sensor for dimming when over 255.
For Gen 5 Lite mirrors, a brightness value of 0-255 overrides the RCD PWM when the RCD is on. A value greater than 255 will disable the PWM override.

Command.Comment: Sets the RCD Brightness

Command.Name: AutoCalMirror
Command.Comment: If no errors occur consider this command successful.

Pointer.Script:
local resp = self:Do( "AutoCal" ).response
if 0x00 == resp then return elseif 0x05 == resp then error( "AutoCal failed. Details: Cal deemed out of range." ) elseif 0x06 == resp then error( "AutoCal failed. Details: Cal deemed out of range and EC was dimmed" ) elseif 0x10 == resp then if ignoreECDimWarning < 1 then error( "AutoCal failed. Details: EC dim failed." ) end elseif 0x11 == resp then error( "AutoCal failed. Details: Ambient sensor failed." ) elseif 0x12 == resp then error( "AutoCal failed. Details: Ambient sensor integration failed." ) elseif 0x13 == resp then error( "AutoCal failed. Details: Glare sensor failed." ) elseif 0x14 == resp then error( "AutoCal failed. Details: Glare sensor integration failed." ) else error( "AutoCal failed. Details: Unknown AutoCal failure." ) end

Command.Name: DumpNVMtoCSV

Pointer.Name: path
Pointer.Comment: Path to dump to

Command.Comment: Dump all NVM to a CSV file given in Path

Pointer.Script:
local dump = io.output( path ) dump:write( "Address,0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7
" ) local addrSize = self:Do( "ReadNVMAddressAndSize" ) -- Read at least 255 bytes from the NVM. local nvmDump = self:Do( "ReadNVM255Bytes", { startingAddress = addrSize.startingAddress, numOfBytes = 255 } ).data if addrSize.size == 512 then local restNmvDump = self:Do( "ReadNVM255Bytes", { startingAddress = addrSize.startingAddress + 255, numOfBytes = 255 } ).data for _, val in ipairs( restNmvDump ) do table.insert( nvmDump, val ) end end
for i = 0, addrSize.size, 8 do local data = { unpack( nvmDump, i + 1, i + 8 ) } print( "Size: " .. #data .. " Data: " .. table.concat( data, "," ) ) if #data == 8 then dump:write( string.format( "0x%04X,%02X,%02X,%02X,%02X,%02X,%02X,%02X,%02X
", i, unpack( data ) ) ) elseif #data == 7 then -- Short by 1 byte when reading 255 bytes. dump:write( string.format( "0x%04X,%02X,%02X,%02X,%02X,%02X,%02X,%02X
", i, unpack( data ) ) ) elseif #data == 6 then -- Short by 2 bytes when reading 512 bytes. dump:write( string.format( "0x%04X,%02X,%02X,%02X,%02X,%02X,%02X
", i, unpack( data ) ) ) elseif #data > 0 then error( "dump size is not consistant." ) end
dump:flush() end
io.close( dump )

Command.Name: OverrideI2C

Pointer.Name: override
Pointer.Comment: 0 = Disable I2C override, 1 = Enable I2C override

Command.Comment: WARNING: Calling this function may cause the I2C to be enables or disabled for a short period of time. Reads and writes the override of the I2C bus. Used to communicate to devices like the RCD using RevComm.

Pointer.ReadScript: self:Do( "ToggleI2COverride" ) return bit.bxor( self:Do( "ToggleI2COverride" ).status, 1 ) -- Call again to toggle back to previous state.
Pointer.WriteScript:
override = bit.bxor( override, 1 ) -- Status currently returns the status of the I2C bus, not the status of Overridden. local stat = self:Do( "ToggleI2COverride" ).status
if stat ~= override then stat = self:Do( "ToggleI2COverride" ).status if stat ~= override then error( "Could not set the I2C Override properly." ) end end

Pointer.Name: setpointInLux
Pointer.Comment: Make this true to set the CalPoint in Lux instead of lux-uS counts

Pointer.Script:
local calAmbient = math.floor( calPoint * ( 1024.0 / 1.0 ) ) -- 1024 counts per 1 lux calAmbient = bit.band( calAmbient, 0xffff ) -- Truncate to a U16.
if setpointInLux < 1 then calAmbient = calPoint -- setpoint is in lux-uS counts end
self:Do( "ConfigureMirror", { cc = 0x31, data = calAmbient } )
